name: Private Room in Canton Townhouse
description: Comfortable and private guest room with a queen size bed, desk, couch, TV, attached bathroom and more, located all by itself on the first floor of a 3 story downtown townhome. Enjoy the privacy of staying on your own floor, coming and going as you please using keypad locks and your own personal pass-code while at the same time enjoying all the comforts of home including a kitchen, living/dining area, covered parking, laundry and a rooftop terrace with a downtown view of the Dallas skyline.
neighborhood_overview: The townhouse is conveniently located downtown directly across from the Dallas Farmers Market with easy access to the Business District, Deep Ellum, the Arts District, West End, Convention Center and the DART.
host_about: Following 15 years tied to a desk, I quit my finance job and decided to take a break from work to go see the world.  I live with my husband Aaron who is a high school Choir Director.  We both share a love of traveling, meeting new people and learning about different places and cultures and for us staying with locals is the only way to travel. During my hiatus from work we are now enjoying the hosting side of Airbnb.  When school is out or on long weekends we will often leave town and rent out our entire home.  When we're in town we rent out our guest room(s).   Collectively, we have visited over 60 countries and nearly all 50 states and are constantly looking for new and exciting places to explore.  We look forward to adding you to our growing list of friends from all over the world whether we are hosting you in our home or visiting yours.

name: Secluded Treasure in the Heart❤️ of the City
description:
Need a staycation? Does working poolside sound good? Escape the bustle of Dallas to your own private Guest House located in a garden setting! Unwind poolside or relax in the hot tub. Guest House includes queen bed, full bath, kitchenette, fast WiFi, TV Netflix/Amazon Prime and MORE! NO CLEANING FEE and no CHECK-OUT CHECKLIST! Check out our discounted weekly/monthly rates! Country in the Heart of the City!

NOTE: We use Airnbnb's Advanced Cleaning Protocol.
neighborhood_overview:
We are located on a quiet and secluded street in the Forest Hills area of Dallas, two minutes away from White Rock Lake, Dallas' Central Park! Five minutes to Casa Linda Plaza (restaurants, bars, massage, grocery store and shopping). Five minutes to trendy Lakewood (great bars, restaurants and shopping). Ten minutes to Lower Greenville (great bars, restaurants and shopping).

Fifteen minutes to downtown Dallas or Uptown. Quick access to the entire Metroplex via Highway 30 or Loop 12 which are both 3 minutes away. Thirty minutes from Love Field and about 40 minutes away from DFW Airport (longer during rush hour).

We are about five minutes away from the Dallas Arboretum, about fifteen minutes away from Fair Park and the Cotton Bowl. Americans Airlines Center and Dallas Arts District are 20 minutes away. Arlington, Texas Rangers baseball and Dallas Cowboys football about 40 minutes away (longer during game days and rush hour).
host_about:

High School Orchestra Teacher 30 years, now retired.

Professional Violist.  Performed all over world with many famous musicians. 

Played in the Ray Price band until Ray's death in 2013.

Like to scuba dive, fish, travel, and camp. 

Have 2 dogs and 3 indoor cats.

neighborhood_overview:
Our location.

We are located in the heart of Dallas in Lakewood. Less than 5 minutes to Lower Greenville and Knox Henderson. Less than 10 minutes to Downtown, Uptown and Deep Ellum.

Easy access to major highways, hospitals and businesses.

Walking distance to Whole Foods, Starbucks, neighborhood restaurants and more.

About the neighborhood.

Lakewood is a vibrant neighborhood in Dallas with trees, greenery and historic mansions.

A quiet, woody neighborhood less than 15 minutes from Downtown Dallas, Lakewood overlooks beautiful White Rock Lake and is home to the Lakewood Country Club.

The area’s homes offer everything from two-bedroom bungalows to vast estates in a variety of architectural styles: Tudor, Colonial, Spanish and French Eclectic are common. Newer homes in the area showcase many different styles including French, Mediterranean, Craftsman, Prairie, and contemporary Mid-Century Modern-styles.

name: Lakewood Private Quarters in the Heart of Dallas
description:
My place is a Private One Bed Room Quarters in a 1930's Tudor in East Dallas Lakewood neighborhood with modern decor, interesting art and tons of amenities. Complimentary drinks, coffee and snacks.
Minutes to shops, coffee, restaurants, Whole Foods grocery store and Harrell Park within walking distance! Five-minute Uber/Lyft ride to downtown, Fair Park, Dallas Arboretum and White Rock Lake. Lakewood is the hottest neighborhood in Dallas. Business travelers welcome. Small town in Big City!
neighborhood_overview: Within the Lakewood neighborhood lies some of the most architecturally significant and historic real estate in the Southwest.  The neighborhood is well-known for its stunning collection of Tudors, Colonials, Mid-Century moderns, Spanish, Mediterranean, Ranch, and Prairie-style homes. and its proximity to downtown Dallas, White Rock Lake and entertainment districts such as Lower Greenville and Deep Ellum.  Lakewood was named one of the 10 best big-city neighborhoods in the United States by CNN and has been noted as a great neighborhood to live by numerous other media sources.
host_about:
Megan and I have been married for 12 years. We have three beautiful kids, ages 10, 8, and 6. Our beautiful home is the home I grew up in!  I am 3rd generation in this 1930's Tudor home.
I have my own Mortgage Team, Theriot Mortgage Group and my wife is an interior designer for Neiman Marcus.
We love hosting events at our home.  We are both very involved in our community and church.
We love raising our kids in the same neighborhood I grew up in.  There is something very special about that.  Lakewood neighborhood is the hottest place for families to move to because of the location right in the heart of Dallas.

description:
Self-check into your private tiny house that holds all you need and only minutes from the Bishop Arts District, the Kessler Theater, and downtown Dallas, all with great shopping and eating.

The Tiny Blue House has everything from a private gated entrance and full kitchen, to a bathroom with barn door access, comfortable seating area, wood floors, and WiFi.

Everything is there to make your stay comfortable an
neighborhood_overview:
Close to Bishop Arts in the best part of Dallas - eclectic, hidden gem, best one of a kind restaurants and shops, diverse, open arms neighborhood, where you can get to anywhere quick - museums, shopping, parks, restaurants.

Walkable areas with easy access. Walking distance to Stevens Park Golf Course and Twelve Hills Nature Center.
host_about: Born and raised in Oak Cliff, I love sharing our beautiful historic neighborhood with guests. Oak Cliff is located just southwest of downtown Dallas with many streets offering a great view of the skyline. Our streets are lined with beautiful mature trees and lovely hills. Travel has always been a passion for me, with my favorite stays in bed and breakfasts. Staying in bed and breakfasts gave me the opportunity to learn the neighborhoods and meet the people. When deciding to build this house, I wanted my guests to feel at home while enjoying the convenience and security of their own private place. We live in the historic Kings Highway neighborhood  which includes the Bishop Arts District. We live just blocks away from The Kessler Theater, the Texas Theater, and the Twelve Hills Nature Center. Dallas is home to great bike & walking trails, Trinity Park, and extensive collection of museums. We provide an easy access to all parts of the city. I'm here and ready to provide ideas and suggestions for places to go, restaurants to try, and sights to see, but will not impose on your privacy. I just want you to have a great time and enjoy your stay in the Tiny Blue House.

name: Trendy, Charming Bungalow in Knox-Henderson
description:
Located in the lively and walkable Knox- Henderson neighborhood, this renovated home built in 1927 has some original charm with updated conveniences. Start your day off with a coffee in our perfect screened-in porch that overlooks our unique zen garden and backyard oasis. Cook in our modern and updated kitchen with Stainless steel appliances, gas stove and beautiful Quartz countertops. The living room includes a comfortable futon couch that converts to a double bed, 42" Smart TV with cable, extra seating, and books and games for entertainment. Sleep like a baby in the master bedroom on a luxurious queen memory foam bed, with 32" Smart TV, large closet, side lamps with USB ports and access to the backyard. The smaller, second bedroom includes a day bed with trundle - great for kids!- as well as a desk with comfortable chair to use as a workspace. The gorgeous bathroom includes a large soaking tub with moveable shower handle, plush towels and bathrobes and hair dryer!

Guests
neighborhood_overview: The house is set two blocks from Henderson Avenue and Lower Greenville, which boast some of Dallas' hottest bars and restaurant. Take a stroll to Velvet Taco for Mexican fare, then head to Candleroom to dance the night away.
host_about:
My husband and I grew up in the Dallas area. We live life in the pursuit of culture, adventure, nature, travel, good books, great wine and excellent food. We have a combined 30+ countries between us and many Michelin star dining experiences. Our personal favorite travel destinations are the British Virgin Islands, South Africa, Japan, Morocco, Iceland and Brazil so far.  We typically use airbnb as travelers as well which gives us great hosting ideas to enhance our listings and guest experiences. 

We are available if you need anything or have any questions during your stay. 

Look forward to hosting (or traveling to you) soon!

Thank you for your time and consideration. 

-D

name: Luxury Bishop Arts Townhome, walk to Arts District
description:
Walk to Bishop Arts with ease!

Don't miss out on this breathtaking Bishop Arts townhouse. Relax on the patio overlooking the backyard while sipping your morning coffee! Walk to local eateries and shopping in the vibrant Bishop Arts neighborhood.

Centrally located, just a quick Uber ride to Downtown Dallas, Uptown, Deep Ellum, Lower Greenville, and Mockingbird Station!
neighborhood_overview:
The hip Bishop Arts District is known for its stylish restaurants & cocktail bars, cool coffee shops, chic fashion stores, and colorful street art.

Some of our favorite restaurants are Eno's Pizza Tavern, Boulevardier (high-end french cuisine), Paradiso (coastal Mediterranean fare), Lockhart BBQ, and SO much more!

Check out the 6 tacos + a bottle of wine special at Tacos y Vino, and be sure to stick around for the weekly Loteria game (Spanish bingo)!

Dance the night away with cocktails at Casablanca!

Pick up a new book and enjoy a hot coffee or glass of wine at The Wild Detectives!

Cult movies are the draw at the Texas Theatre, and Kessler Theater presents live music by local and national bands.

Just a quick drive from neighborhoods Trinity Groves, Downtown Dallas, Uptown, Park Cities, Lower Greenville, Deep Ellum, and more!
host_about:
Whether you're a seasoned traveler or new to the world of Airbnb, I am here to make your experience extraordinary. I take great pride in my role as a property manager and Airbnb Superhost, and I am excited to welcome you to our properties and create a memorable stay for you.
Our Portfolio is carefully selected properties where each one has been thoughtfully curated and meticulously maintained to offer you a comfortable and memorable experience.

name: Fraser Carriage House- Bishop Arts District
description: We are located in the heart of North Oak Cliff. A 6 minute walk to the Bishop Arts District & 2 minute walk to the streetcar which gives you access to downtown Dallas. Guests enjoy the attention to detail & privacy of our carriage house. The home is filled with art from many artists. Outdoor shower is a plus for relaxing in a natural  surrounding. Bring your bluetooth speakers and relax and chill!
neighborhood_overview: Shops, restaurants, bars, and galleries are a minute walk away. Bishop Arts District offers a unique experience. There is a list located in the carriage house manual that lists all restaurants within walking distance. This community thrives on diversity, art, creative spaces, local shop owners, and an eclectic food scene. You will find a variety of vegan/vegetarian, authentic Texas BBQ, and Tex Mex restaurants in the area. Galleries and antiques are also part of this areas unique landscape. Enjoy a cup of coffee in one of our many coffee shops and people watch till the sun goes down. After bar hop along the Bishop Arts street and enjoy live New Orleans jazz or check out the Kessler Theater for live bands. Spas and relaxing foot massage businesses are available if you need to unwind and recharge just within walking distance. Dallas Museum of Art, The Aquarium, Zoo, and Deep Ellum's art district is located downtown. Kay Bailey Hutchinson's Convention Center will cost you an $8 Uber ride.
host_about: We are husband and wife. We've been married for 8 years and have 2 children. Kenji the Corgi is a new member of the family. The Bishop Arts District is our home and we have a strong relationship with our community. Jane is a novice potter and loves hosting. Everett is a Molecular Beam Epitaxy scientist. We have extensive travel experience and enjoy traveling around the world. In our spare time we read, garden, and have a variety of hobbies such as artisan soapmaking, ceramics, painting, woodwork, silk screening, art and book collecting. Everett is an upstate New York native and Jane was born in St. Augustine Florida however has spent most of her life in Dallas, TX.

neighborhood_overview:
Lower Greenville is a major entertainment district in Dallas south of Mockingbird Lane containing many popular bars, restaurants, boutique stores and live music venues.

In the early 20th Century, Greenville Avenue was one of the most important roads in Dallas, serving the new residential areas in East Dallas and playing the part that the North Central Expressway (US 75) plays today.

In the 1910s, Goodwin Avenue was at the far north end of Greenville Avenue and served East Dallas including the Belmont Addition and Vickery Place Addition.

In the 1920s, the Greenland Hills Addition was platted North of Vickery Place, and Mockingbird Lane became the northern boundary of the City of Dallas. Prior to the mid-1920s, Greenville Avenue was known as the "Richardson Road" or the "Richardson Pike".

neighborhood_overview:
Located where the Peak's Addition, Historic Swiss and Bryan Place neighborhoods meet, our Airbnb is possibly in the most centrally located area of Dallas. Easy to get everywhere while still having a cozy feel.

The Peak’s Addition neighborhood is nestled conveniently between Deep Ellum and Lakewood. With over 500 rooftops, our neighborhood boasts architecture from the Queen Anne Victorian Era, Prairie-style, Craftsman, and modern, contemporary architecture as well. The diversity of its homes is as cool as the diversity of its people, and is what makes our neighborhood unique and dynamic.

Peak’s Addition is the closest East Dallas neighborhood to Downtown Dallas and Deep Ellum. Much of our land is protected by the Historic District Overlay and Single Family zoning, securing our neighborhood's future.

Outside of the impressive architecture, some of our greatest assets are the people who live and work here. Most of the people who live in Peak’s Addit

name: 5min to Bishop Arts - Stay at Meadow House
description:
The name "Dallas" is derived from the British 'dol' meaning "meadow" and 'gwas' meaning "dwelling".
Meadow House is a petite guesthouse inspired by Dallas architecture and art museums, native plants to the area, as well as my own travels and heritage from Southeast Asia. Most of the furnishings in Meadow House are vintage, a part of our commitment to reducing consumption while providing a safe and comfortable experience for guests. We're a 5 min drive from the lively Bishop Arts district.
neighborhood_overview:
ome experience the best of Dallas! A bustling cosmopolitan known for our sports, history, BBQ, and frozen margaritas, Dallas is home to more than a dozen neighborhoods and districts that each have their own distinct vibe and attractions. From spectacular museums and performing arts venues in the Arts District to the buzzing nightlife of live music and lively bars, there’s something for everyone here in Dallas! And you will be only a 15 min drive from the heart of Downtown Dallas.

Here are some attractions you won’t want to miss:

✔ The Sixth Floor Museum at Dealey Plaza, located within the former Texas School Book Depository building, a museum that chronicles the life, assassination and legacy of President John F. Kennedy [15 min drive]
✔ Reunion Tower, an iconic Dallas landmark, offers panoramic 360-degree views of the Dallas skyline [15 min drive]
✔ Perot Museum of Nature and Science, a natural history and science museum consisting of two campuses and p
host_about: We are a software designer and developer (we've worked on apps, websites, and even print magazines!) currently living in Dallas, Texas. We love travelling, trying new foods, visiting cute spaces, taking photos, and making new friends. We also run a travel newsletter called The Innbox (theinnbox [dot] guide) that highlights interesting places to stay around the world.

neighborhood_overview:
The historic Swiss Ave neighborhood in Dallas, Texas is a vibrant and bustling area with plenty to see and do. The tree-lined streets are filled with stunning mansions, offering a glimpse into the city's past and present. Visitors can take a leisurely stroll through the neighborhood, admiring the architecture and history on display.

In addition to the beautiful homes, Swiss Ave is home to a variety of attractions that are sure to keep you entertained. For those interested in art and culture, the Dallas Museum of Art is just a short drive away. Nature lovers will enjoy a visit to the Dallas Arboretum and Botanical Gardens, while sports fans can catch a game at AT&T Stadium or American Airlines Center.

With its rich history and diverse range of attractions, Swiss Ave is the perfect destination for anyone looking to explore Dallas.

neighborhood_overview:
West Dallas is a largely residential suburb, known for the landmark Margaret Hunt Hill Bridge, spanning Trinity River. Hip restaurants serve vegan burgers and grain bowls in the Trinity Groves district, also home to galleries showcasing local artists. Trinity Levee Trail is popular with cyclists and joggers for views of the downtown skyline, and Mattie Nash-Myrtle Davis Park has a splashpad and tennis courts.
Trinity grooves is a up-and-coming neighborhood that is undergoing revitalization. We love our neighborhood’s history, and character, and feel perfectly safe here.

neighborhood_overview:
State Thomas is a Dallas Landmark District in the Uptown area of Dallas, Texas. It borders downtown to the south at Woodall Rodgers Freeway, Bryan Place to the east at US 75 (Central Expressway), and LoMac to the north and west.
The State Thomas neighborhood contains the largest collection of Victorian-era homes remaining in Dallas. including the Jacob and Eliza Spake House listed on the National Register of Historic Places. The establishment of the region as a Special Purpose District in 1986 helped make it one of the first new urbanist regions in the city. You will also find many local bars and restaurants scattered through the neighborhood.

You will be walking distance to all the best restaurants in Dallas. One block away from whole foods makes for a easy walk to get groceries. You will also be a short walk to the free trolley cart that gives you free rides up and down McKinney Ave.

The historic Swiss Ave neighborhood in Dallas, Texas is a vibrant and bustling area with plenty to see and do. The tree-lined streets are filled with stunning mansions, offering a glimpse into the city's past and present. Visitors can take a leisurely stroll through the neighborhood, admiring the architecture and history on display.

In addition to the beautiful homes, Swiss Ave is home to a variety of attractions that are sure to keep you entertained. For those interested in art and culture, the Dallas Museum of Art is just a short drive away. Nature lovers will enjoy a visit to the Dallas Arboretum and Botanical Gardens, while sports fans can catch a game at AT&T Stadium or American Airlines Center.

With its rich history and diverse range of attractions, Swiss Ave is the perfect destination for anyone looking to explore Dallas.

The hip Bishop Arts District is known for its stylish restaurants & cocktail bars, cool coffee shops, chic fashion stores, and colorful street art.

Some of our favorite restaurants are Eno's Pizza Tavern, Boulevardier (high-end french cuisine), Paradiso (coastal Mediterranean fare), Lockhart BBQ, and SO much more!

Check out the 6 tacos + a bottle of wine special at Tacos y Vino, and be sure to stick around for the weekly Loteria game (Spanish bingo)!

Dance the night away with cocktails at Casablanca!

Pick up a new book and enjoy a hot coffee or glass of wine at The Wild Detectives!

Cult movies are the draw at the Texas Theatre, and Kessler Theater presents live music by local and national bands.

Just a quick drive from neighborhoods Trinity Groves, Downtown Dallas, Uptown, Park Cities, Lower Greenville, Deep Ellum, and more!

host_about:
Howdy!  

My name is Chase.  I am a father of 4 wonderful boys and husband to a beautiful, AMAZING wife(Colette) of almost 20 years.  OH, and now we have a dog named Ginny, too(she's a chiweenie). 

I love music--ESPECIALLY piano, and my wife and I are known "foodies" in the DFW area.  I own a T-shirt company in Rockwall, and I spend most of my time raising boys and working around the house.

I am an avid traveler, and frequenter of BnBs around the world. 
 But as a native Texan, there's nothing I love more than coming home to these endless Texas skies.  So much open air to breathe and possibilities to explore!

So if we're staying with you, thank you for being a gracious and accommodating host!  And if you're staying with US, I certainly hope you and yours have a wonderful stay and start your days refreshed as you Wake Up in Texas!

neighborhood_overview:
A neighborhood is known for its vibrant street murals, quirky art galleries, and long-time concert venues for indie and blues. Just east of downtown Dallas on the other side of US Route 75, Deep Ellum is the music hub of Dallas. National and local artists perform at the multitude of live music venues across town.

The most popular spots are the Bomb Factory and Trees, along with the Dallas Comedy House that offers entertaining live comedy performances. This neighborhood is a haven for lovers of music and concerts. Public bus stations are located across Deep Ellum, and the neighborhood has very easy access to major highways.

Deep Ellum has more than its fair share of local restaurants and bars. Twisted Root Burger Co., Angry Dog, Braindead Brewing, and Serious Pizza are just a significant few in the area. The music scene, the incredible variety of eateries, luxury apartments, and proximity to downtown Dallas are just a few perks of living in Deep Ellum.

name: *Craftsman's Paradise - 12 Guest Gorgeous Home*
description:
Welcome to Craftsman's Paradise, a luxurious 4 bedroom, 4 bathroom oasis next to the unbeatable Bishop Arts District in Dallas! Our fully renovated home is the perfect getaway for an extended family, a group of friends, or a sports team traveling together with an actual bed for everybody!

We have thought of everything to make your stay a true 5 Star luxury experience including spa-like bathroom amenities, a fully equipped chef's kitchen,outdoor fire pit, full laundry, and a dedicated workspace.
neighborhood_overview: The Bishop Arts District in Dallas is a vibrant and trendy neighborhood known for its charming streets lined with local boutiques, award-winning restaurants, and bustling nightlife. The area is also home to several art galleries, performance spaces, and a historic theater. The district is located just a short drive from downtown Dallas, and it's easy to access by public transportation as well. The Bishop Arts district is a must-see destination for anyone visiting Dallas, whether you're looking to indulge in delicious food, shop for unique gifts, or simply soak up the lively atmosphere.

name: Big&Beautiful 5/4 in Dallas- Hot Tub &Ping Pong
description:
Welcome to your home away from home! Please enjoy!
1. Relax in the hot tub
2. Play ping pong
3. Throw darts
4. Poker tournament
5. Grill something great
6. Compete on NFL Blitz or Marvel Heroes
7. Wii sports anyone?
8. Listen to some smooth vinyl records
9. Enjoy a delicious bottle of wine on us

neighborhood_overview:
This peaceful neighborhood is conveniently located near 75 and Royal Lane.
White Rock walking/biking trail is just at the end of the street. In addition, Orbiter Park tennis courts are a short walk away.

You are:
15-20 minutes from the very BEST Dallas has to offer, including Downtown!
But near your stay you'll find:

*Momo's Italian - Absolutely exquisite Italian cuisine, relaxing atmosphere, and great service

*Mattito's Tex-Mex - A local Dallas legend and a great night out for sure (Get the Bob Armstrong dip!)

*Velvet Taco - a fantastical Taco journey @ Forest Lane and Preston

*Gong-Cha - one of the best Boba Tea places you'll find

*Famous Famiglia - Want pizza delivery? Don't settle for Domino's...call these guys. They're right down the street.

*Lochland's Food & Spirits - Excellent Irish pub with stellar food and kick you in the face cocktails!!! Oh, they do brunch too. (ETA 13 minutes)
host_about:
Howdy!  

My name is Chase.  I am a father of 4 wonderful boys and husband to a beautiful, AMAZING wife(Colette) of almost 20 years.  OH, and now we have a dog named Ginny, too(she's a chiweenie). 

I love music--ESPECIALLY piano, and my wife and I are known "foodies" in the DFW area.  I own a T-shirt company in Rockwall, and I spend most of my time raising boys and working around the house.

I am an avid traveler, and frequenter of BnBs around the world. 
 But as a native Texan, there's nothing I love more than coming home to these endless Texas skies.  So much open air to breathe and possibilities to explore!

So if we're staying with you, thank you for being a gracious and accommodating host!  And if you're staying with US, I certainly hope you and yours have a wonderful stay and start your days refreshed as you Wake Up in Texas!

neighborhood_overview:
The origin of Kessler is named after George Edward Kessler, a landscape architect and city planner whose work heavily influenced Dallas infrastructure.

The Kessler Park neighborhood, which is home to a storied namesake theater, The Kessler, also borders the Trinity River, Lake Cliff and the Bishop Arts District, providing plenty of options for recreation.

Kessler Park is considered one of the best places to live in Texas. Living in this Dallas neighborhood offers residents a dense suburban feel and beautiful hills covered with planned gardens and beautiful houses, which makes it unique because the rest of Dallas is practically a plain.

With a variety of beautiful 20th Century Homes and Mid-Century Modern Homes located in a distinctive Texas geography, Kessler Park is exciting neighborhood for those who enjoy beautiful nature and convenient pathways into the electric life in Downtown Dallas and surroundings.

Deep Ellum has more than its fair share of local restaurants and bars. Twisted Root Burger Co., Angry Dog, Braindead Brewing, and Serious Pizza are just a significant few in the area. The music scene, the incredible variety of eateries, luxury apartments, and the proximity to downtown Dallas are just a few perks of living in Deep Ellum.

neighborhood_overview:
Dallas, Texas, United States

A neighborhood that is known for its vibrant street murals, quirky art galleries, and long-time concert venues for indie and blues. Just east of downtown Dallas on the other side of US Route 75, Deep Ellum is the music hub of Dallas. National and local artists perform at the multitude of live music venues across town. The most popular spots are the Bomb Factory and Trees, along with the Dallas Comedy House that offers live comedy performances. This neighborhood is a haven for lovers of music and concerts. Public bus stations are located across Deep Ellum, and the neighborhood has very easy access to major highways. Deep Ellum has more than its fair share of local restaurants and bars. Twisted Root Burger Co., Angry Dog, Braindead Brewing, and Serious Pizza are just a significant few in the area. The music scene, the incredible variety of eateries and proximity to downtown Dallas are just a few perks of vacationing and/or enjoying long term stays

neighborhood_overview:
Old East Dallas is the perfect destination for visitors looking to experience the city's authentic culture and rich history.

The neighborhood's unique character and vibrant atmosphere are reflected in the many shops, restaurants, and cafes that line its streets.

One of the highlights of Old East Dallas is the popular Dallas Arboretum and Botanical Garden, which is located on the eastern edge of the neighborhood. Here, visitors can enjoy a peaceful walk through beautifully manicured gardens and take in stunning views of White Rock Lake.

If you're a foodie, you'll love the diverse culinary scene in Old East Dallas. The neighborhood has various restaurants, ranging from classic BBQ joints to trendy farm-to-table eateries. Some popular spots include cozy coffee shops and bakeries serving delicious pastries and freshly brewed coffee.

Overall, Old East Dallas is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood that offers something for everyone.

Lake Highlands is a very desirable community in Dallas. Grab a coffee, and try one of a dozen restaurants and dessert shops within walking distance. Or venture just a few miles to get nearly anything else you could want or need in Dallas!

Dallas itself is an incredible destination any time of year. A diverse city known for its thriving arts and culture scene, Dallas has dozens of museums, concert halls and art venues to check out during your stay.
Book a spring trip to the Dallas Blooms Festival at the Dallas Arboretum and Botanical Garden, the largest floral festival in the southwestern US! Come in May for the Dallas International Film Festival, or visit in June for Taste of Dallas and sample dozens of North Texas restaurants. At the tail end of summer, don’t miss the Riverfront Jazz Festival… and come fall, you don’t want to miss the State Fair of Texas—in true Texas style, it’s one of the biggest fairs in the US and lasts for nearly a month.

Lakewood is a vibrant neighborhood in Dallas with trees, greenery and historic mansions.

A quiet, woody neighborhood less than 15 minutes from Downtown Dallas, Lakewood overlooks beautiful White Rock Lake and is home to the Lakewood Country Club.

Our location.

We are located in the heart of Dallas in Lakewood. Less than 5 minutes to Lower Greenville and Knox Henderson. Less than 10 minutes to Downtown, Uptown and Deep Ellum.

Easy access to major highways, hospitals and businesses.

Walking distance to Whole Foods, Starbucks, neighborhood restaurants and more.

About the neighborhood.

Lakewood is a vibrant neighborhood in Dallas with trees, greenery and historic mansions.

A quiet, woody neighborhood less than 15 minutes from Downtown Dallas, Lakewood overlooks beautiful White Rock Lake and is home to the Lakewood Country Club.

The area’s homes offer everything from two-bedroom bungalows to vast estates in a variety of architectural styles: Tudor, Colonial, Spanish and French Eclectic are common. Newer homes in the area showcase many different styles including French, Mediterranean, Craftsman, Prairie, and contemporary Mid-Century Modern-styles.

neighborhood_overview:
You'll be tucked away on a charming tree-lined street with historic homes, diverse cuisine, loads of character and friendly neighbors. Central proximity to Downtown Dallas and a short 5-min ride to Oak Cliff’s eclectic Bishop Arts District. The hip Bishop Arts District is known for its diverse nightlife, chic independent fashion stores and colorful street art. Dining choices range from Texas-style BBQ to Vietnamese pho, while relaxed bars pour everything from cocktails to house-brewed cider. Cult movies are the draw at the Texas Theatre, while the art deco Kessler Theater presents live music by local and national bands.

You also can’t miss checking out Reunion Tower —it looks especially spectacular at night; a MUST see!!!
